Affected Population:
The affected calves are located in a fattening farm in the upper Galilee near the Golan heights.

Outbreak 2 (this report - draft) ( MAS'ADE )
Province/ District/ Unit Type/ Location/ Latitude/ Longitude/ Start date/ End Date
HAZAFON/ Golan/ Not applicable/ MAS'ADE/ 33,2326086451/ 35,7566897447/ 24 Jul 2012/ -

Species/ Measuring units/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ Animals/ 50/ 7/ 0/ 0/ 0
Affected Population:
The herd is a free ranging herd of 50 beef cows. Old skin lesions were also seen on some cows.

Outbreak summary:
Total outbreaks = 2 (Draft)
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 700/ 11/ 0/ 1/ 0

Epidemiology

Epidemiological comments: Before this event the disease was detected in Israel, only in the south of the country in 1989, 2006 and 2007. The herds are located in the north of the country, near the Syrian and Lebanese borders. One [herd] is located in the Golan Heights, and the second in the upper Galilee. The 2 herds are less than 10 km far one of each other. Stomoxys flies have been seen in the area.

Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control Measures

Applied: Quarantine, Movement control inside the country, Modified stamping out.

To be applied: Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)

Country or zone: the whole country

